article.headline: Cincinnati 54, Savannah St. 41
article.story: CINCINNATI -- Yancy Gates scored 12 points and Cashmere Wright added 11 points to lead Cincinnati to a 54-41 victory over Savannah State on Wednesday night. Gates grabbed nine rebounds for the Bearcats (4-0), who won despite shooting 34 percent from the field (18 of 53). Cincinnati led 29-19 at halftime and scored the first six points of the second half for a 35-19 advantage with 17:04 remaining. Rashad Bishop's 3-pointer gave the Bearcats a 41-24 lead with 12:59 to play. They extended it to 48-28 on Gates' jumper with 4:23 left. Ibrahima Thomas added eight rebounds for Cincinnati. This was the fourth of six consecutive home games to open the season for the Bearcats. The Tigers (1-6), who have lost six consecutive games, were 16 of 42 from the field (38.1 percent). Jovonni Shuler led the Tigers, who committed 18 turnovers, with 14 points.
